#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:1
msgid "2.9 (2026-03-01)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:3
msgid "New Linting Checks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:5
msgid ""
"Thirteen new linting checks have been added when using the [`lint`](action-"
"lint) action:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:12
msgid "An overall summary of additions includes:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:14
msgid "Notify use of deprecated configurations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:15
msgid ""
"Notify use of development-mode package configurations for packages which do "
"not configure a development revision."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:17
msgid ""
"Various checks for package/feature-specific configurations when a given "
"package/VCS/feature type is not applicable (e.g. attempting to use Git-"
"related features for a non-Git VCS type package)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:21
msgid ""
"This change drops some warnings that were originally presented in a default "
"releng-tool run to now only show in a lint request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:24
msgid "Support for Development Mode Patching"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:26
msgid ""
"Developers may now utilizing patching support for packages with a "
"[development revision](pkg-opt-devmode-revision). Historically, patches "
"would only be aimed to run for non-development revisions as a way to support"
" delays in patch application for upstream release versions. However, "
"maintainers of a releng-tool project may also experience the same delays "
"when waiting for the application of packages on development streams they "
"cannot control. With this release, developers will have new options to hint "
"whether or not patches are applied to a package no matter what mode is "
"configured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:36
msgid ""
"The default patching strategy has not changed from previous releases. "
"Patches for a package are still automatically detected and applied for non-"
"development revisioned packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:40
msgid ""
"If a developer now wishes to apply patches for a package with a development "
"mode revision, the [`LIBFOO_DEVMODE_PATCHES`](pkg-opt-devmode-patches) "
"option can now be used. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:49
msgid ""
"When operating in [development mode](/guides/development-mode), the `libfoo`"
" package will utilize the `feature/alpha` branch and will automatically "
"apply patches to the cloned sources during the patching stage. The patch "
"configuration also supports pattern matching to have only specific or a "
"wildcard of patches to apply. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:62
msgid ""
"With the ability to support patching packages in development mode, "
"developers utilizing this feature may now need to configure packages to not "
"apply for a standard build. To support this, the configuration option "
"[`LIBFOO_IGNORE_PATCHES`](pkg-opt-ignore-patches) has been introduced. If a "
"developer wants to have new patches applied to only in a development mode "
"context, the following configuration can be used:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:75
msgid ""
"Normal builds will now not apply any patches to `libfoo` by default, and "
"only apply changes when in a development mode. This option also supports "
"patterns to allow ignoring only specific patches for a normal build. For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:86
msgid ""
"For more information on tailoring patch applications for specific "
"development modes, refer to the documentation of the newly added options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:89
msgid "Planned Removals Next Release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:91
msgid ""
"A series of deprecated features are now planned to be removed in a following"
" release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:94
msgid ""
"Bazaar-site support is planned to be removed. Developers can switch to using"
" the Breezy-site type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:96
msgid "Support for Python 3.9 (EOL) will be dropped."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:97
msgid ""
"Package configurations `override_revisions` and `override_sites` will no "
"longer be supported. Developers can take advantage of the "
"[`revisions`](conf-revisions) configuration key or utilize [variable "
"injection](arg-variable-injection) for overriding options on the fly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:102
msgid ""
"The `LIBFOO_SKIP_REMOTE_*` options will be removed as respective "
"`LIBFOO_REMOTE_*` options exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/news/2026-03-01_02.09.00.md:104
msgid ""
"An implicit Python package setup type will no longer be supported. Python-"
"based packages are required to configure [`LIBFOO_PYTHON_SETUP_TYPE`](pkg-"
"opt-python-setup-type)."
msgstr ""
